# Fit Nation — Project Rules

## What This Project Is
Fit Nation is a fitness tracking SaaS app. It has a React web app and a React Native mobile app in a pnpm monorepo. The backend is Laravel with Sanctum auth (REST API, Bearer tokens). The app supports multi-tenant white-label partner branding.

---

## Monorepo Structure
```
fit-nation/
├── apps/
│   ├── web/          ← React 18 + Vite + Ionic + Tailwind (do NOT modify unless asked)
│   └── mobile/       ← Expo React Native app (primary focus)
├── packages/
│   └── shared/       ← shared API, types, schemas, hooks, utils
├── plans/            ← stage-by-stage implementation plans
├── package.json      ← pnpm workspace root
└── pnpm-workspace.yaml
```

---

## Mobile Stack (All Decisions Final)

| Concern | Library |
|---|---|
| Navigation | `@react-navigation/native` + native-stack + bottom-tabs |
| Styling | `nativewind` (Tailwind classNames) |
| Data fetching | `@tanstack/react-query` |
| Forms | `react-hook-form` + `@hookform/resolvers/zod` |
| Validation | `zod` |
| Auth storage | `expo-secure-store` |
| Charts | `react-native-gifted-charts` |
| Animation | `react-native-reanimated` v3 |
| Video | `expo-video` |
| Images | `expo-image` |
| Icons | `lucide-react-native` |
| Theme | `ThemeContext` with `AppColors` object |

**Never suggest alternatives to these. The decisions are made.**

---

## Shared Package (`@fit-nation/shared`)

### What lives here (platform-agnostic code only)
- `src/api.ts` — all API calls (uses `getConfig().baseUrl`, never `import.meta.env`)
- `src/config.ts` — `initApi({ baseUrl })` injection pattern
- `src/auth.ts` — `initAuth({ storage })` injection pattern + `AuthStorage` interface
- `src/types/api.ts` — all TypeScript interfaces and types
- `src/schemas/` — all Zod validation schemas
- `src/hooks/useApi.ts` — all TanStack Query hooks
- `src/utils/` — platform-agnostic utilities only

### What does NOT live here
- Any React Native components
- Any web components
- Framer Motion, CSS variables, PWA utils (web-only)
- `localStorage` or `AsyncStorage` (platform-specific — injected via `initAuth`)

### Import pattern
```ts
import { api, useExercises, useWorkoutSession } from '@fit-nation/shared'
import type { ExerciseResource, WorkoutSessionResource } from '@fit-nation/shared'
```

---

## Key Patterns — Mobile App

### Colors — ALWAYS from ThemeContext
```tsx
// ✅ Correct
const { colors } = useTheme()
<View style={{ backgroundColor: colors.bgBase }} />
<Text style={{ color: colors.textPrimary }} />

// ❌ Never hardcode colors
<View style={{ backgroundColor: '#0F0F0F' }} />
```

### NativeWind — use for layout, ThemeContext for brand colors
```tsx
// ✅ Layout classes via NativeWind
<View className="flex-1 px-6 pt-4 flex-row items-center gap-3" />

// ✅ Dynamic brand colors via inline style
<View className="rounded-2xl p-4" style={{ backgroundColor: colors.bgSurface }} />

// ❌ Don't use hardcoded Tailwind color classes for brand colors
<View className="bg-gray-900" />  // wrong — won't respond to partner theming
```

### Navigation types — always typed
```ts
import type { AppScreenProps } from '../navigation/types'
export function ExerciseDetailScreen({ route, navigation }: AppScreenProps<'ExerciseDetail'>) {}
```

### API initialisation — done once in App.tsx
```ts
// App.tsx
initApi({ baseUrl: process.env.EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL || 'http://localhost:8000/api' })
```

### Auth storage — injected in AuthContext.tsx
```ts
initAuth({
  storage: {
    getItem: (key) => SecureStore.getItemAsync(key),
    setItem: (key, value) => SecureStore.setItemAsync(key, value),
    removeItem: (key) => SecureStore.deleteItemAsync(key),
  }
})
```

### Safe area — always wrap screens
```tsx
import { SafeAreaView } from 'react-native'
<SafeAreaView className="flex-1" style={{ backgroundColor: colors.bgBase }}>
```

### Skeletons — every data-fetching screen
```tsx
if (isLoading) return <SkeletonBox height={100} />
if (isError) return <ErrorState onRetry={refetch} />
```

